passages.text: Strong AI demand with Xaomi- Kingsoft ecosystem a key growth driver; maintain Ow

Kingsoft Cloud reported in line 2Q25 topline growth of \(24\%\) YoY, of which AI continues to be the dominant driver - gross billing for the AI business increased by \(>120\%\) YoY to Rmb729mn and now accounts for \(45\%\) of public cloud business. Adjusted net income was reported at an Rmb300mn loss, versus JPMc - Rmb248mn, with most of the gap lying in the higher- than- expected depreciation cost. We continue to believe Kingsoft Cloud's AI revenue growth outlook has higher certainty than many other AI stocks because of its unique relationship with Xiaomi & Kingsoft group, which are still increasing their demand for GPU compute power for model training, and we think they will allocate a majority of the AI compute spend to Kingsoft Cloud. The gross margin declined YoY due to the introduction of third- party providers for compute power as a result of increasingly complex supply chain management, though we expect it to stabilize on a QoQ basis. We maintain an OW rating on the stock with PTs of US\(19.0 (up from\)18.50)/HK\(10 (unchanged) based on an unchanged 4x 2025E EV/sales multiple.

- AI demand drives revenue growth with Xiaomi becoming a key demand growth driver. Kingsoft Cloud's AI gross billing climbed from Rmb326mn a year ago to Rmb729mn in 2Q25, marking three-digit YoY growth for eight consecutive quarters, and AI now accounts for \(45\%\) of public cloud business. Management sees strong demand ahead, expecting the 2H cloud growth rate to outpace 1H. Revenue from Xiaomi-Kingsoft ecosystem rose \(70\%\) YoY to Rmb629mn in 2Q25, and we expect the ecosystem will rise to become a key demand growth driver for Kingsoft Cloud.

- GPM structurally declined YoY but should stabilize at the current level. Kingsoft Cloud has introduced third-party providers for compute power as a result of increasingly complex supply chain management. As a consequence, the company reported a 2.4pp YoY gross margin decline to \(14.4\%\) . With a stabilizing business structure, we expect the company to maintain its gross margin at c.15% going forward.
